      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An app may use an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsscreen"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object to retrieve information about a screen and use this information to decide what to display on that screen. For example, an app may use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsscreen/1388374-deepestscreen"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method to find out which of the available screens can best represent color and then might choose to display all of its windows on that screen."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Create the application object before you use the methods in this class, so that the application object can make the necessary connection to the window system. You can make sure the application object exists by invoking the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsapplication/1428360-sharedapplication"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsapplication"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". If you created your app with Xcode, the application object is automatically created for you during initialization."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsscreen"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " class is only for getting information about the available displays. If you need additional information or want to change the attributes relating to a display, you must use Quartz Services. For more information, see "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/quartz_display_services"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". "
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        }
      ]
    }
